  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">CSR risks &amp; opportunities in Colombia</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) is an important theme for the Dutch government, inter alia due to its belief that on the long-run CSR will contribute to society&#x2019;s welfare. CSR issues are considered to be an inherent condition for the Dutch aid and trade policy and Dutch embassies play a key role in this regard. For Dutch companies implementing CSR in their business strategy could be an unique selling point. Also addressing CSR issues in Colombia could create business opportunities for Dutch companies. It was also noted that the government communication with Dutch companies about CSR issues could be further improved. Furthermore, it was concluded that the information and tools available to Dutch and Colombian enterprises are in need of an update.In August 2015 a fact finding mission was executed by MVO Nederland and BBO to Colombia to identify the challenges and opportunities of corporate social responsibility (CSR) in Colombia. The objective was to analyse the CSR risks and opportunities by creating a clear insight on the state of CSR across the public and private domain. A second objective was to formulate policy recommendations on CSR in Colombia. Thirdly, existing information are updated and new tools are developed for Dutch companies.</narrative>
  </description>
